WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified optical DNA profile for the Sony FE 24mm f/1.4 G Master lens.
It includes the XA (eXtreme Aspherical) element surface sag formula, the
Nano AR Coating II reflectance characteristics, the Super ED glass achromatic
condition, and the measured distortion, vignetting, and coma behaviour.

WHY IT EXISTS
The G Master series is Sony’s reference for high‑resolution cinema and still
imaging. Knowing the exact aspherical coefficients and coating performance
allows accurate simulation of the lens’s signature—critical for matching
CGI to Sony‑shot plates.

HOW IT WORKS
- Aspherical surface sag: z = (c·r²)/(1+√(1-(1+κ)c²r²)) + A4r⁴ + A6r⁶ + ...
  (XA element precision 0.01 µm).
- Nano AR Coating II: R(λ) → 0 for 400–700 nm via sub‑wavelength nanostructures.
- Super ED glass achromat: 1/(f1·V1) + 1/(f2·V2) ≈ 0 (Abbe Vd > 80 paired
  with standard glass).
- Distortion: k1 = -0.018, k2 = 0.005; vignetting < 1 stop at f/1.4.
- Sagittal coma flare < 0.02 mm at full aperture.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
Same as above; additionally, virtual production on Sony VENICE cameras.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers and L3 Colorists; Sony camera users who need native lens
profiles for ACES ingest.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Ends the practice of using „generic 24mm” profiles for the G Master. Ensures
